metadata.name: Energy Ripples #109
metadata.description:
Three different base patterns, each with multiple styles. 

- From runes, to horizons, to stripes, to chaos.

- Six different ways to combine them.

=================================
FX Hash Features
---------------------------------
pattern_a: 1-5
pattern_b: 1-5
pattern_c: 1-4
combine: 1-6
age: 1-(current year)
offsetX: low, medium, high
offsetY: low, medium, high
scale: low, medium, high
z: low, medium, high (controls 
various properties, for example 
breathing, operations, etc).
=================================

Best enjoyed on full screen / Live mode.

[Return / Enter: save PNG]
[Esc: Pause / Resume animation (while time keeps going)]

metadata.name: Sketching #95
metadata.description:
Rules : 
  1. Start with either a line or a circle from a number of random points in the space.
  2. A line can only spawn a circle at the end. 
  3. A circle can spawn both lines and circles before it completes the full circle.
  4. A circle can sometimes spawn an inner circle.
  5. Smaller elements will spawn randomly along with the lines.

This was inspired by the patterns in Marvel's movie : Eternals. I enjoyed the line growing animation with basic geometry ( line and circle ). Combining this with the rules It generates interesting results.

To add more variety to the rendering, I've added the dash lines in instead of only solid lines. Also the 'lines' consist of thousands of small dots to give it randomness and a bit of texture feeling.

metadata.name: Wanderlust #33
metadata.description:
The intent of this piece is to feed the need of discovery, of venturing into the unknown, tumbling into hidden beauty.

The early morning fog washes away colour and resolution, leaving only silhouettes to guide you. 



Made in Cables.gl

----

Important infos:

-2 Pre-modelled 3d rocks
-Handpainted grass and flowers PNGs as masks
-First couple of frames might flash some weird stuff while all IFs are calculated
-This piece runs on your gpu, and might explode old dusty pcs as i'm not the best in optmization

metadata.name: Sunrise over a Mountain Lake #71
metadata.description:
Painting of the sunrise over a mountain lake, evoking memories of camping trips in the interior of British Columbia. The early sun banishes the lingering traces of the morning mists.

Style inspired by the Canadian 'Group of Seven' landscape paintings of the early 1900's.

metadata.name: Botany #8
metadata.description:
This project started as an exploration of shapes focused on the peaceful feeling that stands out in a floral composition. Amplified by the sketch and toon rendering engine allow the piece to create an infinite amount of satisfying graphic composition.

The piece is draggable and interactive, giving it a sense of tangibility that I find very satisfying. 

It comes in various schemes and styles, each feature is further described in the features section. 

If you are interested in a printed version of your mint, don't hesitate to reach out to me on Twitter so I can render a High resolution and send you a print. 
(Price may vary depending on the demands)

Made in native Webgl and Javascript, by @LodsDorian

metadata.name: Colin #8
metadata.description:
Finally, the avatar project you've all been waiting for. Profile pictures that truly reflect our unique personalities. A chance to show how individual we are.

With a wide range of clothes and hairstyles, expressions ranging from 'Existential Dread' to 'Overwhelming Anxiety', and exciting colours from 'Brilliant Beige' to 'Wonderful Wheat', it's time to bring some sparkle to Web3.


*Please note, all Colin's will almost certainly look the same*


Contact @iamnotwal if you'd like to be added to the Beige-List!


(Layered compositions made possible because of @PureSpider's generously shared template.)

metadata.name: In the Edge #251
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.
